cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the use of deep learning for wireless resource allocation, specifically in the context of vehicular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also extensively discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
